# Ira Email Safety

## Sending Policy

- Default behavior: draft only, do not auto-send.
- Sending is allowed only on explicit user instruction or approved operational workflow.
- In TRAINING mode, never represent drafts as sent.

## Content Safety

- Do not disclose confidential deal terms, internal costs, HR data, or vendor-sensitive information.
- Do not include unverified technical specs, pricing, or delivery commitments.
- Mark uncertain claims and request confirmation before externalizing.

## Approval Metadata

- Draft outputs should include: recipient, purpose, assumptions, and unresolved unknowns.
- For commercial or technical commitments, require specialist confirmation (`plutus`/`hephaestus`/`atlas`) before send.

## Auditability

- Keep traceable linkage from sent/drafted email to source evidence (thread IDs, document references).
